## Summary

| Content | License | Attribution Required? |
|---------|---------|----------------------|
| **BLB text** | Free licensing (Bible Hub) | See berean.bible/licensing.htm |
| **BSB/MSB source tables** | Public Domain | No |
| **TAGNT Greek data** | CC BY 4.0 (STEPBible.org) | **Yes** — credit STEPBible.org and Tyndale House |
| **Strong's lexicons** | CC BY 4.0 (STEPBible.org) | **Yes** — credit STEPBible.org and Tyndale House |
| **Software tools** | MIT | Yes (for software redistribution) |


## Output Data

The output file (`output/blb_interlinear.tsv`) is a derivative work combining
data from multiple sources. Users of the output must comply with all applicable
licenses above. In practice this means:

1. Include the STEPBible CC BY 4.0 attribution when distributing the output
2. Comply with BLB free licensing terms (see http://berean.bible/licensing.htm)
3. The BSB/MSB structural data carries no restrictions


